Package org.lgdcloudsim.datacenter

Class DatacenterSimple

java.lang.Object
org.lgdcloudsim.core.CloudSimEntity
org.lgdcloudsim.datacenter.DatacenterSimple
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<SimEntity>, Runnable, Identifiable, Nameable, SimEntity, Datacenter, DatacenterPrice
public class DatacenterSimple extends CloudSimEntity implements Datacenter
An interface to be implemented by each class that represents a datacenter. See DatacenterSimple for an example of how to implement this interface.
Since:
LGDCloudSim 1.0
Author:
Anonymous

    • intraScheduleFailed

      private void intraScheduleFailed(List<Instance> instances, IntraScheduler intraScheduler, boolean isNeedRevertSelfHostState)
      Handle the failed scheduling results of the InterScheduler. Note that there is no check for scheduling timeout requests here.
      Parameters:
      instances - the failed instances
      intraScheduler - the scheduler corresponding to this scheduling result
      isNeedRevertSelfHostState - whether to revert the state of the host

    • intraScheduleFailed

      private void intraScheduleFailed(List<Instance> instances, IntraScheduler intraScheduler, boolean isNeedRevertSelfHostState, Set<UserRequest> outDatedUserRequests)
      Handle the failed scheduling results of the InterScheduler. The reason why the host state needs to be restored is that after each scheduler schedules an instance, it will default to a successful schedule, and then modify the host state it maintains. Therefore, if the subsequently scheduled instance fails when handling the scheduling conflict, the host state needs to be reverted.
      Parameters:
      instances - the failed instances
      intraScheduler - the scheduler corresponding to this scheduling result
      isNeedRevertSelfHostState - whether to revert the state of the host
      outDatedUserRequests - the outdated user requests that has exceeded the scheduling time limit
